2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes deep neural networks for automated collaborative learning analyses, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the analysis of the collaborative learning process, which involves human-human interactions. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing self-reported questionnaires, which are mentioned as a comparison to the proposed method. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper may involve information retrieval techniques for extracting relevant information from the collaborative learning process, such as identifying key phrases or topics discussed.
